Class Message

    • communication.messages.Message
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Ack, ConsumedAPEvent, ConsumedMPEvent, DestroyedEntityEvent, DisconnectEvent, DisconnectRequest, EndRoundRequest, ExchangeInfinityStoneEvent, ExchangeInfinityStoneRequest, ExtractorGamestateEvent, ExtractorSpawnEntityEvent, GamestateEvent, HealedEvent, MeleeAttackEvent, MeleeAttackRequest, MoveEvent, MoveRequest, Nack, PauseStartEvent, PauseStartRequest, PauseStopEvent, PauseStopRequest, RangedAttackEvent, RangedAttackRequest, Req, RoundSetupEvent, SpawnEntityEvent, TakenDamageEvent, TimeoutEvent, TimeoutWarningEvent, TurnEvent, TurnTimeoutEvent, UseInfinityStoneEvent, UseInfinityStoneRequest, WinEvent
    public class Message
extends java.lang.Object
    The super class of all InGame messages. InGame messages are either requests and have a RequestType or events and have an EventType. The other unused Enum is in both cases null.
    Author:
    Sarah Engele
